Q1. Role of Frontend (FE)

The frontend is the part of a web application that the user sees and interacts with directly. It runs in the browser.

User interface (UI)

Responsible for the look and layout of the website

Includes colors, fonts, buttons, forms, images, and content

Built mainly using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript

Ensures pages are responsive across devices (mobile, tablet, laptop)

User interaction

Handles how users interact with elements (clicks, typing, scrolling, drag-drop)

Validates basic inputs (example: checking if email format is correct before submit)

Provides instant feedback such as error messages, pop-ups, animations

Communication with backend

Sends user requests to backend using API calls (HTTP/HTTPS)

Receives data from backend (for example, user profile or product list)

Often communicates using JSON over REST APIs or GraphQL

Displays the received data to users in a readable form
